<subSubSection id="48EB653FFFEC8A0AF57CF888F7D4D0F6" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="004E36B4FFEC8A0AF57CF888F7D4D0F6" blockId="35.[2733,3540,1674,2243]" lastBlockId="35.[1901,3535,2255,4613]" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF57CF888F3AADE33" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[2736,3119,1833,1872]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="refulgens">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF57CF888F3AADE33" box="[2736,3119,1833,1872]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">Rhinolophus refulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in the 
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF25BF888F251DE33" box="[3479,3540,1833,1872]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF57DF8FFF48EDEE6" box="[2737,2827,1886,1925]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">pusillus</emphasis>
</emphasis>
species group. It was 
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF37CF8FFF2C9DEE6" box="[3248,3404,1886,1925]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">recently</emphasis>
elevated to species status based on genetic data. Although 
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF4B7F866F3D7DE8D" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[2939,3154,1991,2030]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="refulgens">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF4B7F866F3D7DE8D" box="[2939,3154,1991,2030]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">R. refulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF309F866F205DE8D" authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1844" box="[3269,3456,1991,2030]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF309F866F205DE8D" box="[3269,3456,1991,2030]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">R. lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are morphometrically very similar, the genetic divergence between them is higher than that found 
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF457F7C6F3BFD1ED" box="[2971,3130,2151,2190]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">between</emphasis>
other sister species of 
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF529F73DF442D1A0" box="[2789,3015,2204,2243]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF529F73DF447D1A0" box="[2789,3010,2204,2243]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhinolophus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The most recent phylogenetic study has placed 
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF6E5F76EF672D195" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[2345,2551,2255,2294]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="refulgens">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF6E5F76EF672D195" box="[2345,2551,2255,2294]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">R refulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister to 
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF51FF76EF401D195" authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1844" box="[2771,2948,2255,2294]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF51FF76EF401D195" box="[2771,2948,2255,2294]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">R. lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="78E67624FFEC8A0AF439F76EF31CD195" box="[3061,3225,2255,2294]" name="Vietnam" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="78E67624FFEC8A0AF332F76EF24DD195" box="[3326,3528,2255,2294]" name="Cambodia" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
. The taxon 
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF79CF6A5F76CD048" box="[2128,2281,2308,2347]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">cuneatus</emphasis>
is tentatively treated as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF42DF6A5F337D048" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[3041,3250,2308,2347]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="refulgens">
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF42DF6A5F337D048" box="[3041,3250,2308,2347]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">R. refulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the Sumatran specimen has not been comprehensively compared to 
<emphasis id="3285EAA6FFEC8A0AF436F698F31CD003" box="[3066,3225,2361,2400]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">
<taxonomicName id="C7F14D37FFEC8A0AF436F698F311D003" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[3066,3220,2361,2400]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="refulgens">refulgens</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
